{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the resulting output of this layer is a vector with a size equal to 𝑛-𝑠+1 times 𝑎.",
    "The pooling layer employs max pooling to extract the most salient features from each output vector of the convolution layer.",
    "Max pooling selects the highest value among the existing features, considering a pool size of z.",
    "The operation in this layer generates a vector of size 𝑛-𝑠+1𝑧, which can be organised as a matrix of dimensions 𝑎×𝑛-𝑠+1𝑧.",
    "The vectors obtained from the pooling layer are subsequently transformed into 𝑘 distinct categorization categories."
  ]
}